CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1950, pg. 2, reads: "Biggest Night in History - With Ezzard Charles, heavyweight champion, as drawing card, the Centre Avenue branch of the 'Y' staged its biggest report night in history last Friday. The total amount reported was $3,000.  Besides Charles, many other luminaries were present... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, including police officer, standing behind table with sign inscribed "Capt. Louis C. Smith," in Centre Ave YMCA gym
